Problem statement - Term Deposit Subcription ¶

Objective ¶

Using the data collected from existing customers, build a model that will help the marketing team identify potential customers who are relatively more likely to subscribe term deposit and thus increase their hit ratio.

What is a Term Deposit? ¶

A Term deposit is a deposit that a bank or a financial institution offers with a fixed rate (often better than just opening deposit account) in which your money will be returned back at a specific maturity time.

Data Description: ¶

Bank client data:¶

  1. age: Continuous feature
  2. job: Type of job (management, technician, entrepreneur, blue-collar, etc.)
  3. marital: marital status (married, single, divorced)
  4. education: education level (primary, secondary, tertiary)
  5. default: has credit in default?
  6. housing: has housing loan?
  7. loan: has personal loan?
  8. balance in account

Related to previous contact:¶

  1. contact: contact communication type
  2. month: last contact month of year
  3. day: last contact day of the month
  4. duration: last contact duration, in seconds*

Other attributes:¶

  1. campaign: number of contacts performed during this campaign and for this client
  2. pdays: number of days that passed by after the client was last contacted from a previous campaign (-1 tells us the person has not been contacted or contact period is beyond 900 days)
  3. previous: number of contacts performed before this campaign and for this client
  4. poutcome: outcome of the previous marketing campaign Output variable (desired target):
  5. Target: Tell us has the client subscribed a term deposit. (Yes, No)

Insights

Here are the insights drawn from graph before module

From the heatmap its was observed that Pdays and Previous highly correlated (0.45), need to drop one variable for Logistic Regression to avoid multi-collinearity</font>

  • Age - The distribution of age has an extensive age range, from 18 to 95 years old. However, a majority of customers called is around 30 - 50 years old. The distribution of customer age is fairly normal compared to other distributions.
  • Balance - As noted before, distribution of balance has a huge standard deviation relative to the mean, resulting in highly skewed distribution of values. This should be expected in real world scenarios.
  • Duration - The distribution of duration is also highly skewed. The left-skewed boxplot indicates that most calls are relatively short. Also, there is a large number of outliers ranging from 10 minutes to 40 minutes.
  • Month of May has highest count in the data and month of December has the least count.
  • Management, Techician and Blue-Collar jobs comprises majority of the count.
  • Month shows significance differences because April, May, Jun, July, August - shows significant differences in opting the deposits comparing other months this should be important attributes.
  • Day - normally distributed with some fluctuations
  • Job - Management,Blue-collar, technician, retired, admin has higher chances of opting compared to other professions.
  • Marital - Married & single has higher chances of opting comparing divorced.
  • Education - Tertiary education, also known as higher education in some countries - Tertiary and higher shows higher comparing others. Unknown to be treated.
  • Housing - People doest not have housing loan has higher chances of opting.
  • Loan - People doest not have personal loan has higher chances of opting.
  • Contact - People contacted thru cellular has higher chances of opting comparing telephone and unknown. Unknown needs to be treated.
  • Poutcome - Those previous contact unknown has higher chances of opting deposite comparing others. Unknown needs to be treated.
  • Campaign - Those customers who have contacted more than 7 has very less chances of opting deposite. Customers contacted more than 20 times is totally waste of time and money.
  • Previous - Customer not contacted previously befor the campaign has higher chances comparing less than 5 time contacted. Frequent callers (Customer contacted more than 5 has no shows of opting deposite and concentrating them is waste of time and money.)

  • Pdays - 3384 customers opted Term-Deposite who have never contacted or contacted beyond 900 days - shows significant differences.

  • We can see that most people are contacted in the month of MAY.

  • Maximum subcriptions are in the month of MARCH and December.

Its looks like Pdays and Previous highly correlated (0.45), need to drop one variable for Logistic Regression to avoid multi-collinearity</font >

We can verify the result observed above using boxplots.

  • The bottom black horizontal line of blue box plot is called 'minimum' and is calculated as Q1-1.5*IQR.
  • First black horizontal line of rectangle shape of blue box plot is First quartile or 25 percentile.
  • Second black horizontal line of rectangle shape of blue box plot is Second quartile or 50% or median.
  • Third black horizontal line of rectangle shape of blue box plot is third quartile or 75%.
  • Top black horizontal line of rectangle shape of blue box plot is called 'maximum' and is calculated as Q3+1.5*IQR.
  • Small diamond shape of blue box plot is outlier data or erroneous data. Which is below the bottom black horizontal line.

def plot_bivariate(dataframe,target):
    num_var=dataframe.select_dtypes(include='number')
    cat_var=dataframe.select_dtypes(include='object')
    sns.set(font_scale=1.2)
    for column in num_var.columns:
        sns.boxplot(x=dataframe[column],y=dataframe[target])
        plt.show()
    for column in cat_var.columns:
        if column!=target:
            plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))
            sns.countplot(dataframe[column],hue=dataframe[target])
            plt.show()
            
plot_bivariate(pdata,'Target')

 Missing Data Handling ¶
    

  • No null values within the data.
    • 

  • Day - 31 unique days is normal and data normally distributed with some fluctuations
    • 

  • Month - 12 unique month is normal can be used as it is.
    • 

  • Age, day, month, balance, duration, pdays, campaign and previous - numeric no changes
    • 

  • Age is abosolutely fine to have outlaters as retired category has higher potential Term-Deposite customers so will retain as it is.
    • 

  • Job - has been categorized as below : unknown = -1, technician, services, housemain = 3, unemployed & student = 6, self-employed & entrepreneur both same as 7, Blue-Collared & Management 1 & 2 respectively. 
    • 

  • Education - unknown =-1.
    • 

  • Contact - Unknown shows significant differences so will include as different category.
    • 

  • Poutcome - Unknown shows high volume - Others & Unknown both encoded as -1.
    • 

  • Education - Unknown shows significance so retain as it is encoded -1.
    • 

  • Poutcome - Unknown shows significance so retain as it is encoded -1
    • 

  • Marital - OneHotEncoded because single/married/divorced to be used as it is with categories
    • 

  • All object variables (Target,default,housing,loan,job, education, poutcome,month have been converted to int64 & uint8

  Feature Engineering with - Grid Search ¶
Huge difference between Train and Test scores, clearly shows the Train data over fitted.


Need to work on Feature Engineering</font>











Note: - Decision Tree is a non-parametric algorithm and hence prone to overfitting easily. This is evident from the difference in scores in training and testing. In ensemble techniques, we want multiple instances (each different from the other) and each instance to be overfit. Hopefully, the different instances will do different mistakes in classification and when we club them, their# errors will get cancelled out giving us the benefit of lower bias and lower overall variance errors.

Precision and Recall:¶
    

  • Recall: It is the ratio of total number of "Yes" in the label column of the dataset to the number of "Yes" labels does our model detect.
    

    • 

  • Precision: Means how sure is the prediction of our model that the actual label is a "Yes".
    

    • 

  • Here the company wants more people to subscribe to term deposits. So if we have a customer who is willing to subscribe then we shouldn't loose that customer. Therefore focus shpould be on False negative. Decreasing FN and increasing recall.
